{
  "stem": "4189.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I myself was brought into a hospital in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Belgian doctors, of course, took very good care of us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Belgian population was very good to us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They came and visited us and brought us flowers and brought us candy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And, you know, they wanted to be nice to us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I had a friend that lived in Belgium, Johnny Heller.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He had joined the Resistance in Belgium, the resistance, the Belgian resistance.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when the war was over, he volunteered to work in the committee, in that committee that registered all the people that came back from the camps.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when he found my name there, he came right away to the hospital to visit me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- and through him then and through the Belgian Jewish committee that was formed then, the Joint Distribution Committee sent a committee from America, sent it over there to help the people that were liberated, to help them to get settled again.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So through them, we found my brother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My brother was, was able to hide in Belgium in the Ardennes, in the Belgium mountains.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He managed to stay in hiding all throughout the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We also was able to get in touch with my uncle that was in New York, in the United States.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He-- as a matter of fact, he himself had made inquiries through the communities in, in New York to look for us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we in turn did it from Belgium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we found each other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we also found my mother in England.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I was still very weak in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when the time came that they said that I don't need to be in the hospital anymore, they took me out from the hospital.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
